Produced by Sikhya Entertainment and Dharma Productions, the series stars Kritika Kamra, Raghav Juyal, Dhairya Karwa, and Aakash Dixit in lead roles.

writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Paul Dichter,

writer: David Chase, Terence Winter, Mitchell Burgess, Robin Green

description: The trials and tribulations of criminal lawyer Jimmy McGill in the years leading up to and past his fateful run-in with Walter White and Jesse Pinkman.
writer: Vince Gilligan, Peter Gould, Gordon Smith

description: Ishq In The Air is an Indian Hindi-language romantic drama television series directed by Tanmai Rastogi and written by Akshay Jhunjhunwala, Ayush Sharma, Chiranjeevi Bajpai and Riya Poojary. Produced under BBC Studios, it stars Shantanu Maheshwari and Medha Rana.

title: Friends
description: Follows the personal and professional lives of six twenty to thirty year-old friends living in the Manhattan borough of New York City.

description: The Roy family is known for controlling the biggest media and entertainment company in the world. However, their world changes when their father steps down from the company.

genre: Fantasy, Drama, Epic, Action, Adventure, Romance

writer: Ryan J. Condal, George R.R. Martin

title: Silo
description: Men and women live in a giant silo underground with several regulations which they believe are in place to protect them from the toxic and ruined world on the surface.

description: The Jackal is an elusive assassin who makes his living carrying out hits for the highest fee. He soon meets his match in a tenacious British intelligence officer who tracks him down in a thrilling cat-and-mouse chase across Europe.
director: Brian Kirk, Paul Wilmshurst, Anu Menon, Anthony Philipson

title: Severance
description: Mark leads a team of office workers whose memories have been surgically divided between their work and personal lives. When a mysterious colleague appears outside of work, it begins a journey to discover the truth about their jobs.

title: Dune: Prophecy
description: Two Harkonnen sisters combat forces that threaten the future of humankind and establish the fabled sect that will become known as the Bene Gesserit.

title: Yellowstone

title: Shrinking

director: Brett Goldstein, Bill Lawrence, Jason Segel

writer: Brett Goldstein, Bill Lawrence, Jason Segel

title: Schitt's Creek
description: After their business manager embezzles the family fortune, the wealthy Rose family—comprising video store magnate Johnny, his wife and former soap opera actress Moira, and their adult children David and Alexis—lose their wealth and relocate to Schitt's Creek, a town they once purchased as a joke. Now living in a motel, the Roses must adjust to life without money and connect with the town's quirky residents.
writer: Eugene Levy, Dan Levy, David West Read, Michael Short, Kurt Smeaton, Kevin White

title: Money Heist
description: A criminal mastermind who goes by "The Professor" plans the biggest heist in recorded history—to print billions of euros in the Royal Mint of Spain. To help him carry out the ambitious plan, he recruits eight people with certain abilities and who have nothing to lose. The group of thieves take hostages to aid in their negotiations with the authorities, who strategize to come up with a way to capture The Professor. As more time elapses, the robbers prepare for a showdown with the police.
writer: Álex Pina, Esther Martínez Lobato, Javier Gómez Santander

title: Family Business
description: After learning that France is about to legalize cannabis, failed entrepreneur Joseph Hazan decides to convert his late father's kosher butcher shop into the first marijuana coffee shop in France. With the help of his family and friends, Joseph navigates the challenges of starting a new business, dealing with competition, and managing the complexities of family dynamics.
writer: Igor Gotesman, Olivier Rosemberg, Julien War, Jean-André Yerlès

title: Mindhunter
description: In the late 1970s, two FBI agents, Holden Ford and Bill Tench, expand criminal science by delving into the psychology of murder and getting uneasily close to all-too-real monsters. They team up with psychologist Wendy Carr to interview imprisoned serial killers to understand how they think, with the hope of applying this knowledge to solving ongoing cases.
writer: Joe Penhall, Jennifer Haley, Erin Levy, Courtenay Miles

title: The Walking Dead
description: Sheriff's deputy Rick Grimes awakens from a coma to find a post-apocalyptic world dominated by flesh-eating zombies. He sets out to find his family and encounters many other survivors along the way. The group faces numerous challenges, including dealing with other human survivors who have formed dangerous groups and communities.
writer: Frank Darabont, Robert Kirkman, Tony Moore, Charlie Adlard

title: You
description: "You" is a psychological thriller that follows Joe Goldberg, a charming yet dangerously obsessive young man who goes to extreme measures to insert himself into the lives of those he is transfixed by. Utilizing social media and technology, Joe becomes infatuated with various women, leading to intense and often deadly consequences.
writer: Greg Berlanti, Sera Gamble, Caroline Kepnes

title: Emily in Paris
description: Emily Cooper, a young American marketing executive from Chicago, is hired to provide an American perspective at a marketing firm in Paris. As she adjusts to the challenges of life in a foreign city, Emily navigates cultural differences, embarks on new friendships, and explores romantic relationships, all while striving to succeed in her career.

title: Fauda
description: "Fauda" (Arabic for 'Chaos') is an Israeli political thriller that depicts the two-sided story of the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. The series follows Doron Kavillio, a commander of an undercover Israeli unit operating inside Palestinian territories, and his team as they hunt down Hamas terrorist Abu-Ahmed. The narrative also delves into the life of Abu-Ahmed and his family, providing a nuanced perspective on both sides of the conflict.

title: The Serpent
description: "The Serpent" is a crime drama based on the real-life story of Charles Sobhraj, a French serial killer of Indian and Vietnamese descent. Operating in the mid-1970s, Sobhraj preyed on Western tourists traveling through Southeast Asia's "Hippie Trail." The series chronicles his manipulative and murderous exploits, as well as the relentless pursuit by Dutch diplomat Herman Knippenberg, who becomes embroiled in the investigation after a Dutch couple goes missing.

title: One Day
description: "One Day" is a British romantic drama series that chronicles the relationship between Emma Morley and Dexter Mayhew, who meet on their graduation night from the University of Edinburgh on July 15, 1988. The series revisits their lives on the same date each year, capturing the evolution of their friendship and romantic entanglements over two decades.

title: The Night Manager
description: Former British soldier Jonathan Pine, now a night manager at a luxury hotel, is recruited by intelligence operative Angela Burr to infiltrate the inner circle of arms dealer Richard Roper. As Pine delves deeper into Roper's world, he must navigate a web of deceit and danger to bring the criminal to justice.

title: This Is Us
description: "This Is Us" is a heartwarming and emotional story about the Pearson family across multiple generations. The series delves into the lives of parents Jack and Rebecca and their three children—Kevin, Kate, and Randall—exploring their personal struggles, relationships, and connections over various time periods.
writer: Dan Fogelman, Kay Oyegun, Aurin Squire, K.J. Steinberg

title: Panchayat
description: "Panchayat" is a comedy-drama series that follows the journey of Abhishek Tripathi, an engineering graduate who, due to a lack of better job options, becomes the secretary of a panchayat office in the remote village of Phulera, Uttar Pradesh. The series humorously depicts his struggles to adapt to rural life and his interactions with the quirky villagers.

title: Delhi Crime
description: "Delhi Crime" is an Indian crime drama series that follows the Delhi Police's investigation into high-profile crimes in the capital city. The first season is based on the aftermath of the 2012 Delhi gang rape case, depicting the challenges faced by the police in identifying and apprehending the perpetrators. The second season focuses on the resurgence of the notorious Chaddi Baniyan Gang, presenting another intense case for the police force.

title: Mirzapur
description: "Mirzapur" is an Indian action crime thriller that delves into the lawlessness and power struggles in the titular town of Mirzapur, Uttar Pradesh. The series centers on Akhandanand "Kaleen Bhaiya" Tripathi, a wealthy carpet exporter and the mafia don of Mirzapur. His empire is challenged by various forces, leading to violent confrontations and a quest for dominance.
writer: Puneet Krishna, Vineet Krishna, Karan Anshuman, Apurva Dhar Badgaiyan

title: Mismatched
description: "Mismatched" is a coming-of-age romantic drama based on Sandhya Menon's novel "When Dimple Met Rishi." The series follows Dimple Ahuja, an ambitious tech wizard, and Rishi Singh Shekhawat, a traditional romantic, who meet at a summer program. Despite their contrasting personalities and aspirations, they navigate friendship, love, and life's challenges together.

title: Maamla Legal Hai
description: "Maamla Legal Hai" is a legal drama-comedy set in the fictional Patparganj District Court. The series showcases the lives of eccentric lawyers and staff as they navigate quirky cases and uphold justice, often leading to humorous situations.

title: Guns & Gulaabs
description: Set in the 1990s in the cartel-controlled town of Gulaabgunj, "Guns & Gulaabs" follows a lovestruck mechanic, a reluctant heir to a ruling gang, and an honest officer-turned-agent-of-chaos. Their lives intertwine amidst a high-stakes opium deal, leading to a series of comedic power struggles and revenge plots.

title: Kota Factory
description: "Kota Factory" is an Indian Hindi-language television series that follows the life of 16-year-old Vaibhav, who moves to Kota, Rajasthan, an educational hub famous for its coaching centers. The series depicts the life of students in the city and Vaibhav's efforts to get into an Indian Institute of Technology (IIT) by cracking the Joint Entrance Examination.
director: Saurabh Khanna, Arunabh Kumar, Raghav Subbu
writer: Saurabh Khanna, Abhishek Yadav, Puneet Batra, Manoj Kalwani

title: Khakee: The Bihar Chapter
description: "Khakee: The Bihar Chapter" is an Indian crime thriller series that chronicles the high-stakes pursuit between a determined Indian Police Service (IPS) officer, Amit Lodha, and a notorious gang leader, Chandan Mahto, in Bihar. The narrative delves into the complexities of crime and law enforcement in the region, highlighting the challenges faced by officers in maintaining order amidst rampant corruption and crime.

title: Little Things
description: "Little Things" is an Indian romantic comedy series that follows the lives of Kavya Kulkarni and Dhruv Vats, a young couple living together in Mumbai. The series delves into their everyday experiences, exploring themes of love, career aspirations, and personal growth, highlighting the significance of the little moments that constitute a relationship.

title: Masaba Masaba
description: "Masaba Masaba" is a biographical drama series that offers a playful, fictional peek into the lives of real-life mother-daughter duo, fashion designer Masaba Gupta and veteran actress Neena Gupta. The series showcases Masaba's unique background, her foray back into the dating world, and her journey through the diverse worlds of fashion and family.
writer: Sonam Nair, Nandini Gupta, Anupama Ramachandran, Punya Arora

title: Scam 1992: The Harshad Mehta Story
description: "Scam 1992" is a biographical financial thriller that chronicles the meteoric rise and fall of Harshad Mehta, a stockbroker who orchestrated the 1992 Indian stock market scam. The series delves into the intricacies of the financial world, exposing the loopholes in the system and the catastrophic consequences of unchecked ambition.
writer: Sumit Purohit, Saurav Dey, Vaibhav Vishal, Karan Vyas

title: The Family Man
description: "The Family Man" is an action-drama series that tells the story of Srikant Tiwari, a middle-class man who works for a special cell of the National Investigation Agency. While he tries to protect the nation from terrorists, he also has to shield his family from the impact of his secretive, high-pressure, and low-paying job.
writer: Raj Nidimoru, Krishna D.K., Suman Kumar

title: Rocket Boys
description: "Rocket Boys" is a biographical drama series that chronicles the lives of Dr. Homi Jehangir Bhabha and Dr. Vikram Ambalal Sarabhai, two visionary Indian physicists who played pivotal roles in establishing India's nuclear and space programs. The series delves into their personal and professional journeys, highlighting their contributions to science and the nation's development.

title: Pitchers
description: "TVF Pitchers" follows the journey of four friends—Naveen, Jitu, Yogi, and Mandal—who decide to quit their jobs to pursue their startup venture. The series captures the challenges and triumphs they face in the competitive world of entrepreneurship.
writer: Biswapati Sarkar, Talha Siddiqui, Prashant Kumar, Shubham Sharma

title: Sacred Games
description: "Sacred Games" is a neo-noir crime thriller that follows Mumbai police officer Sartaj Singh, who receives a cryptic phone call from the elusive gangster Ganesh Gaitonde, warning him to save the city within 25 days. This sets off a chain of events that delves deep into Mumbai's underworld, exploring themes of crime, corruption, politics, and espionage.
writer: Varun Grover, Smita Singh, Vasant Nath

title: Aarya
description: "Aarya" follows Aarya Sareen, a devoted mother and wife, whose world is turned upside down when her husband is mysteriously killed. Unaware of her husband's involvement in illegal activities, Aarya is forced to join the mafia to protect her family and seek revenge. The series traces her transformation into a formidable mafia queen, balancing her quest for vengeance with the responsibilities of motherhood.

title: Paatal Lok
description: "Paatal Lok" is a crime thriller that follows Inspector Hathi Ram Chaudhary, a disillusioned cop who lands a high-profile case involving an assassination attempt on a prominent journalist. As he delves deeper into the investigation, he uncovers a dark and complex web of crime and corruption, leading him into the metaphorical depths of 'Paatal Lok' (the netherworld).
writer: Sudip Sharma, Sagar Haveli, Hardik Mehta, Gunjit Chopra

title: Industry
description: "Industry" follows a group of young graduates competing for permanent positions at Pierpoint & Co, a prestigious investment bank in London. The series delves into their personal and professional lives as they navigate the high-stakes world of finance, dealing with ambition, power dynamics, and the pressures of the industry.
writer: Mickey Down, Konrad Kay, Sam H. Freeman, Kate Verghese

title: Special OPS
description: "Special OPS" follows Himmat Singh, a senior analyst at the Research and Analysis Wing (RAW), who believes that a single mastermind is behind various terrorist attacks in India over the past two decades. To uncover the truth and prevent future threats, he assembles a covert team of agents to track down the elusive terrorist.
writer: Neeraj Pandey, Deepak Kingrani, Benazir Ali Fida

title: Asur: Welcome to Your Dark Side
description: "Asur: Welcome to Your Dark Side" is a unique crime thriller that pits two opposing worlds against each other. The less explored, intricate world of forensic science and the deep mysticism of ancient Indian mythology. The story follows forensic experts Dhananjay Rajpoot and Nikhil Nair as they navigate a series of gruesome murders that seem to be linked to religious symbolism and rituals.
writer: Gaurav Shukla, Niren Bhatt, Abhijeet Khuman, Pranay Patwardhan

title: Gulak
description: Gullak" is a collection of heartwarming and relatable tales centered around the Mishra family, residing in a small town in India. The series captures the essence of middle-class life through the experiences of Santosh and Shanti Mishra and their sons, Anand "Annu" and Aman, highlighting their daily struggles, aspirations, and familial bonds.

title: Bandish Bandits
description: "Bandish Bandits" follows Radhe Rathod, a Hindustani classical musician, and Tamanna Sharma, a rising pop sensation. Despite their contrasting musical backgrounds, they collaborate, embarking on a journey of self-discovery and exploring whether opposites can adapt and endure together.
writer: Amritpal Singh Bindra, Anand Tiwari, Lara Chandni

title: Criminal Justice
description: "Criminal Justice" is a legal drama series that delves into the Indian criminal justice system. Each season presents a distinct case, exploring the complexities of law and justice. The series offers a gripping narrative that keeps viewers engaged with its intricate storytelling and compelling performances.
writer: Shridhar Raghavan, Apurva Asrani, Rohan Sippy

title: Made in Heaven
description: "Made in Heaven" chronicles the lives of Tara and Karan, two wedding planners in Delhi running an agency named Made in Heaven. The series portrays present-day India as a blend of conservative and modern mindsets, where tradition and modern aspirations often clash, set against the backdrop of lavish and expensive weddings.
writer: Reema Kagti, Zoya Akhtar, Alankrita Shrivastava

title: Inside Edge
description: "Inside Edge" is a sports-drama series that delves into the world of T20 cricket through the fictional team, Mumbai Mavericks. The series exposes the dark underbelly of the sport, highlighting issues like spot-fixing, power struggles, and the interplay of money, fame, and politics within the cricketing world.
writer: Karan Anshuman, Saurav Dey, Ameya Sarda, Nidhi Sharma, Sailesh Ramaswamy

title: The Freelancer
description: "The Freelancer" follows Avinash Kamath, a former police officer turned mercenary, who embarks on a perilous mission to rescue Aliya, a newly married woman trapped in war-torn Syria amidst the rise of ISIS terrorism.

title: Breathe
description: "Breathe" is an Indian crime drama thriller that explores the lives of ordinary men faced with extraordinary circumstances. The series follows Kabir Sawant, a brilliant but unconventional officer of the Crime Branch, who pieces together seemingly unconnected deaths of organ donors, leading to an unlikely suspect—the affable Danny Mascarenhas. The narrative delves into how far one would go to protect the one they love.
writer: Mayank Sharma, Bhavani Iyer, Vikram Tuli, Arshad Syed

title: Kohrra
description: "Kohrra" is a crime thriller series set in Punjab, India. The story begins with the murder of an NRI bridegroom just days before his wedding. As police officers Balbir Singh and Garundi investigate the case, they uncover hidden secrets and familial tensions, delving deep into the complexities of relationships and societal norms.
director: Sudip Sharma, Gunjit Chopra, Diggi Sisodia
writer: Gunjit Chopra, Sudip Sharma, Diggi Sisodia

title: For All Mankind
description: "For All Mankind" is a science fiction drama that explores an alternate history where the Soviet Union succeeds in landing the first human on the Moon, leading to a prolonged and intensified space race. The series delves into the lives of NASA astronauts, engineers, and their families as they navigate the challenges and ambitions of this extended space exploration era.
director: Ronald D. Moore, Matt Wolpert, Ben Nedivi
writer: Ronald D. Moore, Matt Wolpert, Ben Nedivi

title: Black Bird
description: "Black Bird" is a true crime drama based on the autobiographical novel "In with the Devil" by James Keene and Hillel Levin. The series follows Jimmy Keene, who, after being sentenced to 10 years in a minimum-security prison, is offered a chance at freedom. He must enter a maximum-security prison for the criminally insane and befriend suspected serial killer Larry Hall to elicit a confession and discover the whereabouts of his alleged victims.

title: Pachinko
description: "Pachinko" is a sweeping saga that chronicles the hopes and dreams of a Korean immigrant family across four generations as they leave their homeland in an indomitable quest to survive and thrive.

title: Bad Sisters
description: "Bad Sisters" is an Irish black comedy series that follows the Garvey sisters, who are bound together by the premature deaths of their parents and a promise to always protect one another. The series delves into the sisters' lives as they become embroiled in the death of their brother-in-law, leading to an investigation by a determined life insurance agent.
director: Sharon Horgan, Dave Finkel, Brett Baer
writer: Sharon Horgan, Dave Finkel, Brett Baer

title: Foundation
description: "Foundation" is a science fiction series based on Isaac Asimov's seminal book series. It chronicles the monumental journey of a band of exiles who strive to save humanity and rebuild civilization amid the impending fall of the Galactic Empire.

title: The Afterparty
description: "The Afterparty" is a comedy murder mystery series where each episode explores a different character's account of one fateful evening, all told through the lens of popular film genres and unique visuals to match the storyteller's perspective.

title: Servant
description: "Servant" is a psychological horror series that follows a Philadelphia couple, Dorothy and Sean Turner, who hire a young nanny, Leanne Grayson, to care for their newborn son, Jericho. However, as mysterious and supernatural events unfold, the true nature of Leanne and the circumstances surrounding Jericho's arrival are called into question.

title: Hijack
description: "Hijack" is a tense thriller that unfolds in real-time, following the journey of a hijacked plane en route from Dubai to London over a seven-hour flight. Sam Nelson, a skilled corporate negotiator, employs his professional expertise to manage the escalating situation onboard, while authorities on the ground scramble for answers.

title: Mythic Quest
description: "Mythic Quest" is a comedy series that follows the team behind the biggest multiplayer video game of all time. Led by creative director Ian Grimm, the team navigates the challenges of running a successful video game studio, including office politics, creative differences, and the ever-evolving gaming industry.
director: Charlie Day, Megan Ganz, Rob McElhenney
writer: Charlie Day, Megan Ganz, Rob McElhenney

title: The Morning Show
description: "The Morning Show" offers a candid look at the lives of the people who help America wake up in the morning, exploring the unique challenges faced by the team behind a popular morning news program.

title: Dickinson
description: "Dickinson" is a coming-of-age comedy series that audaciously explores the constraints of society, gender, and family from the perspective of rebellious young poet Emily Dickinson. Set in the 19th century, it blends historical settings with modern sensibilities, delving into themes of identity, artistic expression, and societal norms.

title: Monarch: Legacy of Monsters
description: Following the battle between Godzilla and the Titans that leveled San Francisco, the series tracks two siblings uncovering their family's connection to the secretive organization known as Monarch. Their journey delves into the world of monsters and reveals buried secrets spanning three generations.

title: Bad Monkey
description: The series follows Andrew Yancy (Vince Vaughn), a former Miami Police Department detective demoted to a health inspector in the Florida Keys. Yancy becomes embroiled in a complex investigation after a tourist discovers a severed human arm, leading him into a world of greed, corruption, and a mischievous monkey.

title: Manhunt
description: The aftermath of the first American presidential assassination and the fight to preserve and protect the ideals that were the foundation of Lincoln's Reconstruction plans.

title: Orange Is the New Black
description: The series follows Piper Chapman (Taylor Schilling), a woman in her 30s living in New York City, who is sentenced to 15 months in Litchfield Penitentiary, a minimum-security women's federal prison. This sentence results from her conviction for transporting a suitcase full of drug money for her then-girlfriend Alex Vause (Laura Prepon), an international drug smuggler. \n

title: The Office
description: "The Office" is a mockumentary sitcom that humorously depicts the daily lives of employees at the Dunder Mifflin Paper Company in Scranton, Pennsylvania. Led by the eccentric regional manager Michael Scott, the series explores workplace culture, relationships, and the antics of its diverse cast of characters.
writer: Ricky Gervais, Stephen Merchant, Greg Daniels

title: Normal People
description: "Normal People" is an Irish romantic psychological drama that follows Marianne Sheridan and Connell Waldron, two individuals from a small town in Ireland, as they navigate the complexities of their relationship from their final days in secondary school to their undergraduate years at Trinity College. The series delves into themes of love, friendship, and the impact of social class on personal connections.

title: Girls
description: Girls is an American comedy-drama series that follows the lives of four young women—Hannah, Marnie, Jessa, and Shoshanna—as they navigate their twenties in New York City. The show delves into their personal and professional challenges, relationships, and the often humorous realities of young adulthood.
writer: Lena Dunham, Jenni Konner, Judd Apatow

title: Love Is Blind
description: Love Is Blind is a reality dating series where singles seek to form emotional connections without seeing each other. Participants converse in separate "pods," and if a connection leads to a proposal, they meet face-to-face for the first time. The engaged couples then navigate their relationships in the real world, culminating in a decision at the altar to marry or part ways.

title: Too Hot to Handle
description: Too Hot to Handle is a British reality dating game show where a group of singles known for engaging in casual flings are placed together in a tropical resort. Under the supervision of a virtual assistant named "Lana," they must abstain from any kissing, sexual contact, or self-gratification. Each infraction reduces the $100,000 grand prize, encouraging participants to form deeper emotional connections.

title: Sex Education
description: Sex Education is a British teen comedy-drama series that follows Otis Milburn, a socially awkward high school student, who teams up with his classmate Maeve Wiley to set up an underground sex therapy clinic at their school. Drawing from the expertise of his mother, Jean Milburn, a professional sex therapist, Otis provides guidance to his peers on various sexual and relationship issues. The series delves into the complexities of teenage life, exploring themes of identity, intimacy, and personal growth.
writer: Laurie Nunn, Alice Seabright, Sophie Goodhart

title: Conversations with Friends
description: Conversations with Friends is an Irish television series based on Sally Rooney's novel of the same name. It follows Frances and her best friend Bobbi, two college students in Dublin, as they form an unexpected connection with married couple Melissa and Nick. The series delves into complex relationships, exploring themes of love, friendship, and self-discovery.
writer: Alice Birch, Mark O'Halloran, Meadhbh McHugh, Susan Soon He Stanton

title: Two and a Half Men
description: Two and a Half Men is an American sitcom that follows the life of Charlie Harper, a wealthy and carefree jingle writer with a penchant for alcohol and women. His relaxed lifestyle is disrupted when his divorced brother, Alan, and Alan's young son, Jake, move into his Malibu beach house. The series humorously explores the dynamics of this unconventional household, highlighting the brothers' contrasting personalities and the challenges of raising Jake.
writer: Chuck Lorre, Lee Aronsohn, Don Foster

title: Grey's Anatomy
description: Grey's Anatomy is a medical drama series that follows the personal and professional lives of surgical interns, residents, and attendings at the fictional Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital in Seattle. The series centers on Dr. Meredith Grey and her colleagues as they navigate complex medical cases and intricate relationships, balancing the challenges of the medical field with their personal lives.
writer: Shonda Rhimes, Krista Vernoff, Stacy McKee

title: How I Met Your Mother
description: How I Met Your Mother is an American sitcom that follows Ted Mosby recounting to his children the events leading up to his meeting their mother. Set in New York City, the series delves into the lives of Ted and his close-knit group of friends—Marshall, Lily, Barney, and Robin—as they navigate relationships, careers, and personal growth.

title: Sex and the City
description: Sex and the City is an American romantic comedy-drama television series that follows the lives of four women—Carrie Bradshaw, Samantha Jones, Charlotte York, and Miranda Hobbes—as they navigate love, friendship, and careers in New York City. The series delves into contemporary social issues, including sexuality, femininity, and societal expectations, all through the lens of their enduring friendship.
writer: Darren Star, Michael Patrick King, Jenny Bicks, Cindy Chupack, Amy B. Harris

title: Veep
description: Veep is an American political satire comedy series that follows Selina Meyer, the Vice President—and later President—of the United States, as she navigates the complexities and absurdities of American politics. Alongside her dysfunctional staff, Selina strives to leave a lasting legacy while contending with the daily challenges and scandals inherent in political life.
writer: Armando Iannucci, Simon Blackwell, Tony Roche, David Mandel

title: Arrow
description: Arrow follows billionaire playboy Oliver Queen, who, after being presumed dead for five years following a shipwreck, returns to Starling City. Transformed by his experiences, he becomes the vigilante known as "The Hood," later adopting the moniker "Green Arrow," aiming to combat crime and corruption in his city. The series delves into Oliver's dual life, balancing his public persona with his secret identity, and features flashbacks revealing his time on the island Lian Yu and other locations.
director: Greg Berlanti, Marc Guggenheim, Andrew Kreisberg
writer: Greg Berlanti, Marc Guggenheim, Andrew Kreisberg

title: Modern Family
description: Modern Family is an American sitcom that offers a humorous look at the lives of the diverse Pritchett-Dunphy-Tucker clan. Presented in a mockumentary style, the series explores the complexities of modern family life through the experiences of patriarch Jay Pritchett, his children, and their families, addressing various social and cultural issues with wit and warmth.

title: Platonic
description: Platonic is a comedy series that follows former best friends Sylvia and Will, who reconnect after a long rift. As they approach midlife, their renewed friendship becomes increasingly consuming, leading to humorous and destabilizing effects on their lives.

title: The Essex Serpent
description: The Essex Serpent is a British gothic romance period drama that follows London widow Cora Seaborne (Claire Danes) as she moves to Essex to investigate reports of a mythical serpent. She forms a surprising bond of science and skepticism with the local vicar, Will Ransome (Tom Hiddleston). When tragedy strikes, the locals accuse her of attracting the creature.

title: Five Days at Memorial
description: Five Days at Memorial is a disaster medical drama miniseries that chronicles the harrowing events at a New Orleans hospital in the aftermath of Hurricane Katrina. As floodwaters rise, power fails, and heat soars, exhausted caregivers are forced to make unimaginable decisions over five days that will haunt them for years to come.

title: Scam 2003: The Telgi Story
description: Scam 2003: The Telgi Story is a biographical financial thriller that delves into the life of Abdul Karim Telgi, the mastermind behind one of India's most ingenious schemes—the counterfeit stamp paper scam. Originating from Khanapur in Karnataka, Telgi's operation spanned multiple states, shaking the entire nation with its audacity and scale.

title: Aashram
description: Aashram is an Indian Hindi-language crime drama web series that delves into the life of Baba Nirala, a self-proclaimed godman whose outward benevolence masks a web of criminal activities, including exploitation, corruption, and manipulation of his devotees. The series explores themes of blind faith, power dynamics, and societal issues, as law enforcement and journalists strive to unveil the truth behind the facade.
writer: Madhvi Bhatt, Avinash Kumar, Sanjay Masoomm, Tejpal Singh Rawat, Kuldeep Ruhil

title: Jamtara – Sabka Number Ayega
description: Jamtara – Sabka Number Ayega is an Indian crime drama series that follows a group of young men in the small town of Jamtara, Jharkhand, who run a successful phishing scam. Their operation attracts the attention of a corrupt politician seeking a share of the profits and a determined police superintendent aiming to dismantle the racket.
writer: Trishant Srivastava, Kanishka Singh Deo, Ashwin Verman, Nishank Verma

title: Apharan
description: Apharan is an Indian crime thriller series centered on Rudra Srivastava, a senior inspector with the Uttarakhand police. Initially entangled in a kidnapping plot at the behest of the victim's stepmother, Rudra finds himself ensnared in a complex web of deceit and conspiracy, leading to unforeseen consequences and challenges that test his morality and resolve.

title: The Witcher
description: The Witcher is a fantasy drama series that follows Geralt of Rivia, a solitary monster hunter, as he struggles to find his place in a world where people often prove more wicked than beasts. Destiny intertwines him with powerful sorceress Yennefer of Vengerberg and young Princess Ciri, who harbors a dangerous secret. Together, they navigate a volatile world where humans, elves, witchers, gnomes, and monsters battle to survive and thrive, and where good and evil are not easily identified.
writer: Lauren Schmidt Hissrich, Declan de Barra, Beau DeMayo, Sneha Koorse, Haily Hall, Mike Ostrowski

title: The Night Agent
description: The Night Agent is an American action thriller series that follows Peter Sutherland, a low-level FBI agent assigned to a covert emergency line in the White House basement. His mundane role takes a dramatic turn when a distress call plunges him into a vast conspiracy that reaches the highest levels of government. Partnering with cybersecurity expert Rose Larkin, Peter must navigate a treacherous web of espionage to protect the nation.

title: Murder Mindfully
description: Murder Mindfully is a German dark comedy thriller that follows Björn Diemel, a lawyer entangled with the mafia, who seeks a better work-life balance through mindfulness classes. Applying these new techniques, he inadvertently discovers that murder becomes a surprisingly effective coping strategy, leading him down a path of darkly humorous self-discovery.

title: Messiah
description: Messiah is an American thriller series that follows CIA officer Eva Geller as she investigates a charismatic figure known as Al-Masih, who gains international attention through acts that disrupt public order. As his followers claim he performs miracles, global media becomes captivated by this enigmatic individual. Geller races to uncover whether he is a divine entity or a cunning con artist capable of destabilizing the world's geopolitical balance.

title: Silicon Valley
description: Silicon Valley is an American comedy series that follows Richard Hendricks, a shy computer programmer, who develops a revolutionary data compression algorithm. Alongside his quirky friends, he establishes a startup called Pied Piper in the competitive tech hub of Silicon Valley. The series humorously explores the challenges and absurdities of startup culture, corporate politics, and the tech industry's eccentric personalities.
director: Mike Judge, John Altschuler, Dave Krinsky
writer: Mike Judge, John Altschuler, Dave Krinsky, Alec Berg, Clay Tarver, Dan O'Keefe, Carson Mell, Rob Turbovsky, Carrie Kemper, Adam Countee

title: Collateral
description: Collateral is a four-part British television drama that follows Detective Inspector Kip Glaspie as she investigates the seemingly random murder of a pizza delivery driver in London. As she delves deeper, she uncovers a complex web of interconnected characters, including drug dealers, smugglers, and spies, revealing a conspiracy that challenges her understanding of the crime.

title: Bodyguard
description: Bodyguard is a British political thriller that follows Police Sergeant David Budd, a war veteran suffering from PTSD, now working as a Specialist Protection Officer for London's Metropolitan Police Service. Assigned to protect the ambitious Home Secretary Julia Montague, whose politics he opposes, Budd finds himself torn between his duty and beliefs as he becomes embroiled in a complex web of political intrigue and danger.

title: Tehran
description: Tehran is an Israeli spy thriller that follows Tamar Rabinyan, a Mossad hacker-agent who infiltrates Tehran under a false identity to help destroy Iran's nuclear reactor. When her mission fails, Tamar must plan an operation that will place everyone dear to her in jeopardy.
director: Moshe Zonder, Omri Shenhar, Dana Eden, Maor Kohn

title: Fleabag
description: Fleabag is a British comedy-drama that offers a window into the mind of a dry-witted, grief-riddled woman navigating life and love in London. Known only as Fleabag, she uses humor and a no-filter attitude to cope with personal tragedy and complex relationships, often breaking the fourth wall to share her unfiltered thoughts with the audience.

title: 30 Rock
description: 30 Rock is a satirical sitcom that offers a behind-the-scenes look at the chaotic world of television production. The series follows Liz Lemon, the head writer of a live sketch comedy show called "TGS with Tracy Jordan," as she navigates the challenges of managing eccentric actors, a demanding network executive, and her own personal life. The show is renowned for its sharp wit, rapid-fire humor, and meta-commentary on the entertainment industry.
writer: Tina Fey, Robert Carlock, Jack Burditt, John Riggi, Matt Hubbard, Kay Cannon, Ron Weiner, Tracey Wigfield, Luke Del Tredici, Josh Siegal, Dylan Morgan

title: The Summer I Turned Pretty
description: The Summer I Turned Pretty is a coming-of-age romantic drama that follows Isabel "Belly" Conklin, a teenager who spends her summers at Cousins Beach with her family and the Fisher family. This particular summer marks a turning point as Belly finds herself in a love triangle with brothers Conrad and Jeremiah Fisher, leading to experiences of first love, heartbreak, and personal growth.
writer: Jenny Han, Gabrielle Stanton, Sarah Kucserka

title: Euphoria
description: Euphoria is an American teen drama that follows a group of high school students as they navigate a world filled with drugs, sex, trauma, and social media. The series centers on Rue Bennett, a 17-year-old recovering drug addict struggling to find her place in the world.

title: Freaks and Geeks
description: Freaks and Geeks is an American teen comedy-drama that chronicles the lives of two siblings, Lindsay and Sam Weir, as they navigate the social challenges of high school in the early 1980s. Lindsay, a former "mathlete," attempts to break away from her goody-two-shoes image by befriending a group of "freaks," while her younger brother, Sam, and his friends embody the quintessential "geeks." The series delves into the trials and tribulations of adolescence, exploring themes of identity, acceptance, and the desire to fit in
writer: Paul Feig, Judd Apatow, Mike White, J. Elvis Weinstein, Jeff Judah, Gabe Sachs, Patty Lin, Jon Kasdan, Bob Nickman, Rebecca Kirshner

title: Parks and Recreation
description: Parks and Recreation is a mockumentary-style sitcom that follows Leslie Knope, a dedicated and optimistic public official in the Parks Department of the fictional town of Pawnee, Indiana. The series humorously explores local government dynamics, community projects, and the personal lives of its quirky employees as they strive to make their city a better place.
writer: Greg Daniels, Michael Schur, Alan Yang, Harris Wittels, Aisha Muharrar, Katie Dippold, Dan Goor, Norm Hiscock, Megan Amram, Chelsea Peretti

title: Chernobyl
description: Chernobyl is a historical drama miniseries that meticulously recounts the events surrounding the 1986 nuclear disaster at the Chernobyl Nuclear Power Plant in the Soviet Union. The series delves into the explosion's immediate aftermath, the subsequent cleanup efforts, and the harrowing human stories of those who risked their lives to mitigate the catastrophe. It highlights the systemic failures and the devastating human cost of the disaster.

title: The Kominsky Method
description: The Kominsky Method follows Sandy Kominsky, an aging actor who once enjoyed a brief moment of success and now works as a revered Hollywood acting coach. Alongside his longtime agent and friend, Norman Newlander, Sandy navigates the challenges of growing older in Los Angeles, dealing with personal losses, health issues, and the complexities of relationships, all while maintaining a sense of humor.
writer: Chuck Lorre, Al Higgins, David Javerbaum

title: Parenthood
description: Parenthood is an American family drama series that follows the lives of the Braverman family, comprising an older couple, their four adult children, and their respective families. Set in Berkeley, California, the show delves into the complexities of family dynamics, parenting challenges, personal growth, and the everyday struggles and joys that come with raising children and maintaining relationships.
writer: Jason Katims, Sarah Watson, Kerry Ehrin, Bridget Carpenter

title: Kaos
description: Kaos is a British mythological dark comedy series that offers a contemporary reimagining of Greek mythology. The narrative follows three mortals as they uncover their intertwined destinies amidst the capricious whims of the Greek gods. The series delves into themes of power, gender politics, and the human condition, all while presenting the deities in a modern, often satirical light.

title: Glow
description: GLOW is a comedy-drama series set in 1980s Los Angeles, following Ruth Wilder, an out-of-work actress who finds an unexpected chance at stardom when she joins the world of women's wrestling. Alongside a group of misfits, she reinvents herself as part of the Gorgeous Ladies of Wrestling, navigating the challenges of the sport and the entertainment industry.

title: Ramy
description: Ramy follows Ramy Hassan, a first-generation Egyptian-American Muslim, as he embarks on a spiritual journey in his politically divided New Jersey neighborhood. The series delves into the challenges of balancing faith, family expectations, and personal desires, offering a nuanced portrayal of the American Muslim experience.
director: Ramy Youssef, Ari Katcher, Ryan Welch
writer: Ramy Youssef, Ari Katcher, Ryan Welch

title: Ozark
description: Financial advisor Marty Byrde relocates his family from Chicago to the Missouri Ozarks after a money-laundering scheme goes wrong. To appease a drug boss, he must launder $500 million in five years, entangling his family in dangerous criminal activities.
writer: Bill Dubuque, Mark Williams, Chris Mundy

title: Grace and Frankie
description: Grace Hanson, a retired cosmetics mogul, and Frankie Bergstein, a free-spirited artist, are shocked when their husbands reveal they are in love with each other and plan to get married. The two women, who have never been close, form an unexpected bond as they navigate the challenges of starting over in their 70s.

title: The Newsroom
description: The series chronicles behind-the-scenes events at the fictional Atlantis Cable News (ACN) channel, focusing on anchor Will McAvoy and his staff as they set out to produce a news show "in the face of corporate and commercial obstacles and their own personal entanglements."

title: House of Cards
description: After being passed over for the position of Secretary of State, Congressman Frank Underwood embarks on a ruthless political ascent with the help of his equally ambitious wife, Claire. Together, they navigate the treacherous landscape of Washington, D.C., employing manipulation, betrayal, and power plays to achieve their goals.
writer: Beau Willimon, Michael Dobbs, Andrew Davies

title: The White Lotus
description: "The White Lotus" is a sharp social satire following the exploits of various guests and employees of the fictional White Lotus resort chain. As the series progresses, each passing day reveals a darker complexity in these picture-perfect travelers, the hotel's cheerful employees, and the idyllic locale itself.

title: Black Mirror
description: "Black Mirror" is a British anthology series that explores a twisted, high-tech multiverse where humanity's greatest innovations and darkest instincts collide. Each episode is a standalone narrative delving into themes of modern society, particularly concerning the unanticipated consequences of new technologies.

title: BoJack Horseman
description: Set in a world where anthropomorphic animals and humans coexist, "BoJack Horseman" follows the life of BoJack, a washed-up 1990s sitcom star. Struggling with addiction, depression, and self-destructive behavior, BoJack attempts to navigate his personal and professional life while seeking meaning and redemption.
writer: Raphael Bob-Waksberg, Kate Purdy, Joe Lawson, Mehar Sethi, Joanna Calo, Elijah Aron, Jordan Young

title: The Circle
description: "The Circle" is a reality competition series where contestants live in separate apartments within the same building and communicate exclusively through a unique social media platform called "The Circle." They can present themselves in any way they choose, either as themselves or by adopting a completely different persona, a tactic known as "catfishing." Throughout the game, players rate each other, and the most popular players become "Influencers," while the least popular risk being eliminated or "blocked." The ultimate goal is to be the last contestant standing and win a cash prize.

title: RuPaul's Drag Race
description: "RuPaul's Drag Race" is a reality competition series where drag queens from across the United States compete in various challenges, including fashion, acting, and performance, to be crowned "America's Next Drag Superstar." Hosted by RuPaul, the show has become a cultural phenomenon, celebrating the art of drag and LGBTQ+ culture.

title: Gilmore Girls
description: "Gilmore Girls" follows the lives of single mother Lorelai Gilmore and her academically ambitious daughter, Rory, in the charming town of Stars Hollow, Connecticut. The series delves into their relationships, personal aspirations, and the unique dynamics of their small-town community.
writer: Amy Sherman-Palladino, Daniel Palladino, Jennifer Heath, Sheila R. Lawrence

title: Diff'rent Strokes
description: "Diff'rent Strokes" is an American sitcom that follows the lives of Arnold and Willis Jackson, two African-American brothers from Harlem who are taken in by wealthy Park Avenue businessman Phillip Drummond after their mother's passing. The series explores the cultural and social adjustments the boys face as they integrate into a predominantly white, affluent environment, often addressing serious issues such as racism, drug use, and child abuse.
writer: Ben Starr, Martin Cohan, Howard Leeds

title: Frasier
description: "Frasier" is a spin-off of the sitcom "Cheers," following Dr. Frasier Crane as he returns to his hometown of Seattle to host a radio call-in show. Living with his father, Martin, a retired police officer, and interacting with his brother, Niles, and producer, Roz, Frasier navigates the complexities of family, friendship, and his own neuroses.
director: David Angell, Peter Casey, David Lee
writer: Christopher Lloyd, Joe Keenan, David Lloyd

title: Everybody Loves Raymond
description: "Everybody Loves Raymond" centers on Ray Barone, a sportswriter living in Long Island, New York, with his wife Debra and their three children. Ray's parents, Frank and Marie, and his brother Robert live across the street, leading to frequent family interactions filled with humor and conflict.
writer: Philip Rosenthal, Ray Romano, Tucker Cawley

title: The Recruit
description: "The Recruit" follows Owen Hendricks, a young CIA lawyer who becomes entangled in dangerous international conflicts when a former asset threatens to expose her relationship with the agency. As he navigates the treacherous world of espionage, Owen must balance his legal responsibilities with the perilous demands of covert operations.
writer: Alexi Hawley, Amelia Roper, Hadi Deeb, Maya Goldsmith

title: The Crown
description: "The Crown" is a historical drama that chronicles the reign of Queen Elizabeth II, depicting the political rivalries, personal relationships, and significant events that shaped the second half of the 20th century. The series begins with Elizabeth's marriage to Philip, Duke of Edinburgh, in 1947 and progresses through key moments of her reign, offering an intimate portrayal of the British monarchy.

title: Manifest
description: "Manifest" follows the passengers and crew of Montego Air Flight 828, who experience a brief period of severe turbulence during their flight from Jamaica to New York City. Upon landing, they discover that over five and a half years have passed, during which time they were presumed dead. As they reintegrate into society, they begin to experience mysterious voices and visions, referred to as "callings," guiding them toward various tasks and challenges.

title: Black Doves
description: "Black Doves" is a British spy thriller that follows Helen Webb, portrayed by Keira Knightley, who leads a double life as the wife of the Secretary of State for Defence and as a covert operative for a clandestine organization known as the Black Doves. When her lover is murdered by London's underworld, Helen's secret identity is at risk. To protect her and uncover the truth, the Black Doves enlist Sam Young, an old friend and assassin, played by Ben Whishaw. The series delves into themes of espionage, betrayal, and the complexities of leading a double life.

title: Surviving Black Hawk Down
description: "Surviving Black Hawk Down" is a three-part docuseries that delves into the 1993 Battle of Mogadishu, offering perspectives from both American soldiers and Somali individuals involved. The series features interviews with U.S. Army Rangers, Delta Force soldiers, Somali fighters, and civilians, providing a comprehensive account of the events and their aftermath.

title: Full Swing
description: "Full Swing" is an immersive documentary series that follows professional golfers on and off the course during a season of relentless competition. It provides a behind-the-scenes look at the lives of top PGA Tour players, capturing their personal and professional challenges, triumphs, and the high-stakes world of professional golf.
director: Box Media Studios, Box to Box Films
writer: Box Media Studios, Box to Box Films

title: Cobra Kai
description: Decades after their 1984 All Valley Karate Tournament bout, a middle-aged Daniel LaRusso and Johnny Lawrence find themselves martial-arts rivals again.
director: Josh Heald, Jon Hurwitz, Hayden Schlossberg
writer: Josh Heald, Jon Hurwitz, Hayden Schlossberg

title: Apple Cider Vinegar
description: "Apple Cider Vinegar" is a six-part Australian drama miniseries that chronicles the rise and fall of Belle Gibson, a wellness influencer who falsely claimed to have cured her brain cancer through alternative medicine. The series delves into her deceit, the impact on her followers, and the broader implications of misinformation in the wellness industry.
writer: Samantha Strauss, Anya Beyersdorf, Angela Betzien

title: American Primeval
description: Set in 1857 during the Utah War, "American Primeval" explores the violent collisions of cultures, religions, and communities as they fight for control of the American West. The series follows Sara Rowell (Betty Gilpin) and her son Devin as they navigate the treacherous landscape, seeking safe passage to reunite with her husband. They enlist the help of Isaac Reed (Taylor Kitsch), a man raised by the Shoshone, who becomes their guide through the perilous frontier.

title: Nobody Wants This
description: An agnostic sex podcaster and a newly single rabbi fall in love; discovering if their relationship can survive their wildly different lives and meddling families.
writer: Erin Foster, Craig DiGregorio, Jenni Konner, Bruce Eric Kaplan

title: Escape at Dannemora
description: Based on the true story of the 2015 Clinton Correctional Facility escape in upstate New York, the series follows inmates Richard Matt and David Sweat, who are aided in their escape by Joyce "Tilly" Mitchell, a married prison employee entangled in relationships with both men. Their breakout leads to a massive manhunt, uncovering a web of deceit and manipulation within the prison system.
writer: Brett Johnson, Michael Tolkin, Jerry Stahl

title: Bridgerton
description: Set in Regency-era London, "Bridgerton" follows the eight close-knit siblings of the Bridgerton family as they navigate high society in search of love and happiness. The series delves into the intricacies of London's aristocracy, exploring themes of romance, societal expectations, and scandal, all narrated by the mysterious Lady Whistledown.

title: Ripley
description: Set in 1960s New York, "Ripley" follows Tom Ripley, a struggling con artist hired by a wealthy man to retrieve his wayward son from Italy. As Tom becomes entangled in the opulent lifestyle of his target, he embarks on a complex journey of deceit, fraud, and murder.

title: Wednesday
description: "Wednesday" follows the titular character, Wednesday Addams, as she navigates her life at Nevermore Academy, a boarding school for outcasts. While honing her emerging psychic abilities, she attempts to solve a supernatural mystery that embroiled her parents 25 years ago, all while dealing with the complexities of teenage life.

title: Prime Target
description: Edward Brooks, a brilliant mathematics postgraduate at Cambridge University, is on the verge of a groundbreaking discovery—a pattern in prime numbers that could potentially access every computer system worldwide. As he delves deeper into his research, he becomes the target of a shadowy organization intent on destroying his work. Teaming up with NSA agent Taylah Sanders, Edward embarks on a perilous journey to uncover a high-stakes conspiracy that threatens global security.\n

title: Acapulco
description: "Acapulco" follows the journey of Máximo Gallardo, a young man in 1984 whose dream comes true when he lands a job at the most luxurious resort in Acapulco, Las Colinas. However, he soon realizes that the job is far more complicated than expected. Told through flashbacks, the series features an older Máximo, played by Eugenio Derbez, narrating his past experiences in a heartfelt and comedic way.
director: Austin Winsberg, Eduardo Cisneros, Jason Shuman
writer: Austin Winsberg, Eduardo Cisneros, Jason Shuman

title: The Lincoln Lawyer
description: "The Lincoln Lawyer" follows Mickey Haller, a defense attorney in Los Angeles who operates his practice from the back of his Lincoln Navigator. Navigating complex legal cases, Mickey often finds himself entangled in personal and professional challenges that test his moral compass and legal acumen.
writer: David E. Kelley, Ted Humphrey, Michael Connelly

title: Indian Police Force
description: "Indian Police Force" follows Delhi Police Officer Kabir Malik as he confronts a formidable adversary, Zarar, who has embraced terrorism. The series delves into Malik's relentless pursuit of justice, highlighting the challenges and sacrifices inherent in law enforcement.

title: Thukra Ke Mera Pyaar
description: Set in Uttar Pradesh, the series explores the love story between Kuldeep, a young man from a modest background, and Shanvika, a girl from an influential and wealthy family. Their relationship faces challenges due to societal expectations and deep-rooted issues of caste and class. As their romance blossoms, they encounter fierce opposition, particularly from Shanvika's powerful family, determined to keep them apart.

title: Citadel: Honey Bunny
description: Set in late 1990s and early 2000s India, "Citadel: Honey Bunny" explores the origins of Nadia Sinh's parents, Honey and Bunny. The series follows stuntman Bunny, who recruits struggling actress Honey for a side gig, thrusting them into a high-stakes world of espionage and betrayal. Years later, as their dangerous past catches up with them, the estranged couple must reunite to protect their young daughter, Nadia.
writer: Raj Nidimoru, Krishna D.K., Sita R. Menon

title: Taaza Khabar
description: "Taaza Khabar" follows Vasant "Vasya" Gawade, a sanitation worker whose life takes an unexpected turn when he acquires a magical device capable of predicting the future. As Vasya navigates the challenges and opportunities brought about by this newfound power, he embarks on a journey that tests his relationships, ambitions, and moral compass.\n

title: The Legend of Hanuman
description: "The Legend of Hanuman" is an Indian animated series that chronicles the journey of Hanuman, the revered monkey god, as he transforms from a mighty warrior into a divine figure. The series delves into his adventures, challenges, and the pivotal role he plays in the epic tale of Ramayana, showcasing his evolution into a beacon of hope amidst darkness.
director: Sharad Devarajan, Jeevan J. Kang, Charuvi Agrawal
writer: Sharad Devarajan, Sarwat Chaddha, Ashwin Pande, Arshad Syed

title: Maamla Legal Hai
description: Set in the bustling District Court of Patparganj, "Maamla Legal Hai" is a legal dramedy that follows a team of eccentric lawyers and staff as they navigate quirky cases and personal challenges. Led by the charismatic Advocate Visheshwar D. Tyagi, the ensemble tackles a variety of legal disputes, blending humor with courtroom drama.

title: Killer Soup
description: Set in the fictional hill station of Mainjur, Tamil Nadu, "Killer Soup" follows Swathi Shetty, an ambitious but unskilled nurse-turned-home chef. Desperate to fulfill her dream of opening a restaurant, Swathi conspires to replace her husband, Prabhakar Shetty, with her lover and Prabhakar's doppelgänger, Umesh Pillai. The series delves into the chaotic and darkly comedic events that ensue as their plan unfolds.
director: Abhishek Chaubey, Unaiza Merchant, Harshad Nalawade
writer: Abhishek Chaubey, Harshad Nalawade, Anant Tripathi, Unaiza Merchant

title: Maamla Legal Hai
description: Set in the bustling District Court of Patparganj, "Maamla Legal Hai" is a legal dramedy that follows a team of eccentric lawyers and staff as they navigate quirky cases and personal challenges. Led by the charismatic Advocate Visheshwar D. Tyagi, the ensemble tackles a variety of legal disputes, blending humor with courtroom drama.

title: Shekhar Home
description: Set in the early 1990s in the tranquil town of Lonpur, Bengal, "Shekhar Home" follows the enigmatic detective Shekhar and his housemate, ex-army doctor Jayavrat Saini, as they solve a series of intriguing mysteries. Their partnership delves into cases ranging from blackmail and murder to supernatural occurrences, all while a shadowy figure known as "M" watches Shekhar from the shadows.

title: Sapne vs Everyone
description: "Sapne Vs Everyone" follows the journey of two passionate dreamers, Prashant Narula and Jimmy Mehta, who clash against societal norms, personal aspirations, and each other's ambitions. As they navigate the challenges of expectations and morality, their intertwined paths explore the relentless pursuit of dreams amidst resistance and personal dilemmas.

title: Raat Jawan Hai
description: "Raat Jawaan Hai" is a modern and quirky series that delves into the lives of three inseparable childhood friends—Avinash, Radhika, and Suman—as they navigate the challenges of modern-day parenthood. Balancing their deep-rooted friendship with the unpredictable nature of raising children, the series offers a heartfelt exploration of contemporary issues faced by millennials.

title: Poachers
description: "Poacher" is an Indian Malayalam-language crime drama miniseries that delves into the grim world of ivory poaching in Kerala's forests. Set in 2015, the series is inspired by true events involving transnational crime syndicates and the subsequent government crackdown known as Operation Shikkar. The narrative follows a group of Indian Forest Service officers, NGO workers, police constables, and Good Samaritans who risk their lives to track down the most notorious elephant ivory poachers in India's history and bring them to justice.

title: Maharani
description: "Maharani" is a political drama series set in Bihar, India. The story centers around Rani Bharti, a homemaker whose life takes an unexpected turn when she is appointed as the Chief Minister of Bihar. The series delves into her journey as she navigates the murky waters of politics, challenges patriarchal norms, and strives to bring about change in a male-dominated society.
writer: Singh Nandan, Uma Shankar Singh, Subhash Kapoor

title: Kaala Paani
description: "Kaala Paani" is a survival drama thriller set in the Andaman and Nicobar Islands. The series follows a diverse group of individuals who find themselves in a desperate fight for survival when a mysterious illness descends upon the islands. As they race to find a cure, their intertwined destinies reveal deep human connections amidst the unfolding crisis.
writer: Biswapati Sarkar, Nimisha Misra, Sandeep Saket, Amit Golani

title: Freedom at Midnight
description: "Freedom at Midnight" is a historical drama series adapted from the bestselling book by Larry Collins and Dominique Lapierre. The series delves into the events leading up to the Partition of India and Pakistan, exploring the religious and socio-political dynamics of the era. It provides a detailed account of the final years of British rule in India, highlighting the challenges and negotiations faced by key figures during this pivotal period.
writer: Abhinandan Gupta, Gundeep Kaur, Adwitiya Kareng Das, Divy Nidhi Sharma, Revanta Sarabhai, Ethan Taylor

title: Black Warrant
description: "Black Warrant" is a crime drama series based on the 2019 non-fiction book "Black Warrant: Confessions of a Tihar Jailer" by Sunil Gupta and Sunetra Choudhury. The series offers a gritty portrayal of life inside Tihar Jail during the early 1980s, seen through the eyes of rookie jailer Sunil Gupta. It delves into the challenges he faces, including corruption, gang rivalries, and interactions with notorious criminals like Charles Sobhraj.

title: Dus June ki Raat
description: "Dus June Kii Raat" follows the story of Bhagyesh, nicknamed 'Panauti' due to his notorious bad luck. Determined to revive his late father's theater, Menka, he embarks on a journey filled with comedic misadventures alongside his cousin, Battu. Their lives take a turn when they meet Puppy, leading to a series of mysterious and humorous events.

title: Khalbali Records
description: "Khalbali Records" is an Indian Hindi-language musical drama series that delves into the clash between indie and commercial music, framed through a father-son rivalry within the competitive music industry.

title: Honeymoon Photographer
description: "Honeymoon Photographer" is an Indian crime thriller series that follows Ambika Nath, a photographer hired to document a honeymoon in the Maldives. The trip takes a dark turn when the groom, Adhir, is found dead, and Ambika becomes the prime suspect. As she grapples with memory loss from the night of the incident, Ambika must navigate a web of deceit and secrets to uncover the truth and clear her name.

title: Doctors
description: "Doctors" is a British medical soap opera that aired on BBC One from March 26, 2000, to November 14, 2024. Set in the fictional West Midlands town of Letherbridge, the series follows the lives of the staff at both an NHS doctor's surgery and a university campus surgery, as well as their families and friends. The show delves into both their professional challenges and personal relationships, addressing a wide range of medical and social issues.

title: Doctors
description: "Doctors" is an Indian Hindi-language medical drama series that delves into the lives of newly appointed resident doctors, surgeons, nurses, and terminally ill patients at the Elizabeth Blackwell Medical Centre in Mumbai. Central to the narrative are resident doctor Nitya Vasu, who joins with a motive for revenge, and neurosurgeon Dr. Ishaan Ahuja, whom Nitya believes is responsible for her brother Dhawal's botched surgery.

title: 36 Days
description: "36 Days" is an Indian Hindi-language crime thriller series that unravels the mysterious death of Farah Zaidi, a newcomer to a suburban housing complex in Goa. The narrative moves backward, exploring the 36 days leading up to her demise, exposing the hidden secrets and intricate relationships of the residents.

title: Murshid
description: "Murshid" is a Hindi crime thriller series that follows the story of Murshid Pathan, a retired gangster who is compelled to return to his criminal past when his family is threatened by his former ally, Farid. As Murshid delves back into the underworld to protect his loved ones, he faces intense rivalries and confronts buried secrets.

title: Mithya
description: "Mithya" is an Indian Hindi-language psychological thriller web series that explores themes of deceit, revenge, manipulation, and retribution. The story begins with Juhi Adhikari, a Hindi literature professor in Darjeeling, accusing her student, Rhea Rajguru, of plagiarism. This accusation spirals into a complex web of lies and deceit, leading to unforeseen consequences for both women. The second season, titled "Mithya: The Darker Chapter," delves deeper into the sinister bond between Juhi and Rhea, intensifying their psychological battle.

title: The Railway Men
description: "The Railway Men" is an Indian Hindi-language historical drama miniseries that portrays the heroic efforts of railway workers during the 1984 Bhopal gas tragedy. The series focuses on the courageous actions of station master Iftekaar Siddiqui and his team at Bhopal Junction railway station, who risked their lives to save thousands from the catastrophic gas leak at the Union Carbide plant.

title: Bada Naam Karenge
description: "Bada Naam Karenge" is a romantic drama series that follows Rishabh Rathi and Surbhi Gupta, a modern Gen-Z couple navigating the complexities of an arranged marriage. Set across two timelines—a past lockdown encounter in Mumbai and present family meetings in Madhya Pradesh—the series explores the challenges they face as past secrets resurface, testing their bond amidst familial expectations and cultural norms.

title: Pyaar Testing
description: "Pyaar Testing" is a romantic comedy-drama that follows Dhruv and Amrita, two individuals introduced as prospective marriage partners. To assess their compatibility, they decide to live together before their wedding, challenging societal norms and sending shockwaves through their conservative families. The series explores the dynamics of modern relationships, love, and the influence of traditional values.

title: Anupama
description: "Anupamaa" follows the journey of a devoted housewife and mother who has dedicated her life to her family, often at the cost of her own aspirations. As she faces continuous disrespect and challenges within her household, Anupamaa embarks on a path of self-discovery, striving for independence and self-respect.

title: On Call
description: "On Call" is an American police procedural and serial drama that follows veteran training officer Traci Harmon and her rookie partner Alex Diaz as they respond to emergency calls on the streets of Long Beach, California. The series delves into the complexities of modern policing, highlighting the personal and professional challenges faced by officers in a diverse urban environment.
writer: Tim Walsh, Elliot Wolf, Molly Manning, Bryan Gracia, Tiffany Bratcher, John Conley

title: Paradise
description: "Paradise" is an American political thriller set in a city-sized underground bunker in Colorado, three years after a doomsday event. The series follows Secret Service Agent Xavier Collins as he investigates the assassination of the President of the United States within this enclosed society, uncovering deep-seated conspiracies and challenging the facade of their utopian existence.
writer: Dan Fogelman, John Hoberg, Molly Manning, Bryan Gracia, Tiffany Bratcher, John Conley

title: Win or Lose
description: "Win or Lose" is Pixar's first original animated series, focusing on a co-ed middle school softball team called the Pickles during the week leading up to their championship game. Each of the eight episodes presents the same events from the unique perspective of a different character, including players, their parents, and even the umpire, offering a multifaceted view of the team's dynamics and individual experiences.

title: Zero Day
description: "Zero Day" is a political thriller series that follows former U.S. President George Mullen, portrayed by Robert De Niro, who is called out of retirement to lead an investigation into a catastrophic cyberattack that has devastated the nation. As he delves deeper, Mullen uncovers a complex web of lies and conspiracies, challenging his perception of truth and trust in a world where disinformation runs rampant.
director: Eric Newman, Noah Oppenheim, Michael S. Schmidt
writer: Eric Newman, Noah Oppenheim, Michael S. Schmidt, Roberto Patino, Dee Johnson, Eli Attie

title: Brian and Maggie
description: "Brian and Maggie" is a Channel 4 dramatization that revisits the infamous 1989 television interview between journalist Brian Walden and Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher. The series delves into the complex relationship between the two, highlighting how their final interview became a pivotal moment leading to Thatcher's resignation and the end of their friendship.

title: Good American Family
description: "Good American Family" is a true crime drama inspired by the real-life story of Natalia Grace. The series follows Kristine and Michael Barnett, a Midwestern couple who adopt Natalia, a young girl with a rare form of dwarfism. As they integrate her into their family, they begin to question her age and background, leading to a complex web of legal and emotional challenges. The narrative is presented from multiple perspectives, exploring themes of perspective, bias, and trauma.
writer: Katie Robbins, Sarah Sutherland, Eoghan O'Donnell, Jaquen Tee Castellanos, Samantha Levenshus

title: Yellowjackets
description: "Yellowjackets" is a thriller drama series that follows a high school girls' soccer team whose plane crashes in the remote northern wilderness in 1996. The narrative oscillates between their harrowing survival ordeal and the present day, where the now-adult women grapple with the traumatic aftermath of their experience.
writer: Ashley Lyle, Bart Nickerson, Jonathan Lisco, Ameni Rozsa, Sarah L. Thompson, Chantelle Wells

title: Mare of Easttown
description: In a small Pennsylvania town, Detective Mare Sheehan investigates a local murder while her personal life crumbles around her.

title: Downton Abbey
description: Set in the early 20th century, "Downton Abbey" follows the lives of the aristocratic Crawley family and their servants on the fictional Yorkshire estate of Downton Abbey. The series explores the impact of historical events on British society and the family's dynamics.
writer: Julian Fellowes, Shelagh Stephenson, Tina Pepler

title: The InBESTigators
description: A group of clever school kids—Maudie, Ezra, Ava, and Kyle—form their own detective agency, solving mysteries in their school and neighborhood while vlogging about their adventures.
writer: Robyn Butler, Wayne Hope, Molly Daniels, Lisa Marie Corso, Maddy Butler, Jayden Masciulli, Bob Franklin

title: Sherlock
description: "Sherlock" is a British crime drama television series that presents a contemporary adaptation of Sir Arthur Conan Doyle's Sherlock Holmes detective stories. Set in modern-day London, it follows the brilliant detective Sherlock Holmes and his friend Dr. John Watson as they solve complex cases that baffle the police.
writer: Steven Moffat, Mark Gatiss, Stephen Thompson

title: Supergirl
description: "Supergirl" follows Kara Zor-El, Superman's cousin, who, after years of hiding her powers on Earth, decides to embrace her superhuman abilities and become the hero she was destined to be. Balancing her life as a reporter and a protector of National City, Kara faces numerous challenges, including alien threats and personal dilemmas.
director: Ali Adler, Greg Berlanti, Andrew Kreisberg
writer: Ali Adler, Greg Berlanti, Andrew Kreisberg

title: Doraemon
description: "Doraemon" follows a robotic cat from the 22nd century who travels back in time to assist a young boy named Nobita Nobi. Using futuristic gadgets from his four-dimensional pocket, Doraemon helps Nobita navigate various challenges, aiming to improve his future.
writer: Manami Sakurai, Higashi Shimizu, Kimihito Ito, Yosuke Suzuki, Isao Murayama, Teruko Uchiumi

title: Monk
description: "Monk" follows Adrian Monk, a former San Francisco police detective whose obsessive-compulsive disorder and numerous phobias intensified after the unsolved murder of his wife, Trudy. Despite his condition, Monk's keen observational skills and sharp memory make him an exceptional consultant for the police, solving complex cases with the help of his assistants and former colleagues.
writer: Andy Breckman, Hy Conrad, David Breckman, Daniel Dratch, Tom Scharpling

title: Line of Duty
description: Line of Duty follows AC-12, an anti-corruption unit investigating police misconduct in a fictional British police force. Led by Superintendent Ted Hastings, the team, including DS Steve Arnott and DI Kate Fleming, delves into cases involving corrupt officers and their connections to organized crime. As they uncover deeper layers of conspiracy, they face increasing dangers and political pressure.

title: Surface
description: This psychological thriller follows Sophie Ellis, portrayed by Gugu Mbatha-Raw, who suffers extreme memory loss after a traumatic head injury. As she embarks on a quest to reconstruct her life with the assistance of her husband and friends, Sophie begins to question the authenticity of her seemingly perfect existence.
writer: Veronica West, Lillian Yu, Peter Calloway, Dan Lee West, Cortney Norris

title: WeCrashed
description: "WeCrashed" chronicles the meteoric rise and subsequent fall of WeWork, a startup that grew from a single coworking space into a global brand valued at $47 billion. Central to this narrative are the company's charismatic co-founder, Adam Neumann, and his wife, Rebekah, whose personal and professional dynamics played a pivotal role in the company's trajectory.
writer: Lee Eisenberg, Drew Crevello, Elissa Karasik, Eva Anderson, Zenzele Price, Mark Stasenko, Eleanor Burgess

title: Lady in the Lake
description: Set in 1960s Baltimore, the series follows Maddie Schwartz, a housewife who transitions into investigative journalism after a tragic event. As she delves into the disappearance of a young girl, Maddie's path intersects with Cleo Sherwood, a dedicated activist striving to advance the agenda of Baltimore's Black community. Their intertwined journeys navigate the complexities of race, class, and social justice.

title: Dope Thief
description: Dope Thief follows two lifelong friends from Philadelphia, Ray and Manny, who impersonate DEA agents to rob a country house. Their small-time scam escalates into a life-and-death situation as they inadvertently expose a major narcotics corridor on the East Coast.

title: Suits LA
description: Suits LA follows Ted Black, a former federal prosecutor from New York, who relocates to Los Angeles to establish a law firm specializing in criminal and entertainment law. As he navigates the complexities of the West Coast legal scene, Ted confronts personal and professional challenges, including managing high-profile clients and internal power struggles within his firm.

title: Sugar
description: Sugar follows John Sugar, an enigmatic private detective in Los Angeles, grappling with personal demons as he investigates the disappearance of a Hollywood producer's beloved granddaughter. As the case unfolds, unexpected twists challenge his perceptions and reveal deeper mysteries.

title: Disclaimer
description: Disclaimer follows Catherine Ravenscroft, a renowned documentary filmmaker whose life unravels when she discovers she is a key character in a novel that reveals a dark secret she has kept hidden. As the narrative unfolds, Catherine confronts her past and the repercussions of her actions, leading to a tense psychological thriller that explores themes of guilt, memory, and the subjective nature of truth.

title: Masters of the Air
description: Masters of the Air chronicles the experiences of the 100th Bomb Group, known as the "Bloody Hundredth," during World War II. This miniseries delves into the harrowing missions of American bomber crews as they undertake perilous flights over Nazi-occupied Europe, bringing the war directly to Hitler's doorstep. The narrative captures the camaraderie, courage, and sacrifices of these young airmen, highlighting their pivotal role in the aerial campaign against Germany.

title: Dark
description: Dark is a science fiction thriller set in the fictional German town of Winden. The series begins with the mysterious disappearance of a teenager, leading to the exposure of hidden secrets among four interconnected families. As the story unfolds, it delves into a complex time travel conspiracy that spans multiple generations, exploring the existential implications of time and its effect on human nature.

title: The Vampire Diaries
description: Set in the fictional town of Mystic Falls, Virginia, The Vampire Diaries follows Elena Gilbert, a teenage girl who becomes entangled in the supernatural world after meeting two vampire brothers, Stefan and Damon Salvatore. As she navigates complex relationships and uncovers the town's hidden secrets, Elena confronts various supernatural threats, including witches, werewolves, and original vampires.

title: The Originals
description: The Originals is a spin-off of The Vampire Diaries, focusing on the Mikaelson siblings: Klaus, Elijah, and Rebekah. As the original vampires, they return to New Orleans—a city they helped build centuries ago—to reclaim control and protect their family legacy.
