The series delves into their complex relationships, power struggles, and the supernatural politics of the French Quarter, involving witches, werewolves, and other vampires.
writer: ulie Plec, Michael Narducci, Marguerite MacIntyre

title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
description: Brooklyn Nine-Nine is a comedic series that follows the exploits of Detective Jake Peralta and his diverse, lovable colleagues as they police the NYPD's 99th Precinct. The ensemble cast navigates various cases and personal challenges under the leadership of the no-nonsense, unflappable Captain Raymond Holt.

title: Suits
description: On the run from a drug deal gone bad, brilliant college dropout Mike Ross finds himself working with Harvey Specter, one of New York City's best lawyers.
writer: Aaron Korsh, Sharyn Rothstein, Genevieve Sparling, Marshall Knight

title: Dexter: Original Sin
description: The series chronicles Dexter's formative years in Miami, highlighting his internal battle with his emerging homicidal tendencies. Guided by his adoptive father, Harry Morgan, Dexter adopts a code to target those who evade justice. As he begins a forensic internship at Miami Metro Police Department, Dexter learns to conceal his true nature while navigating personal and professional challenges.

title: Dupahiya
description: Dhadakpur, the Belgium of Bihar, is on the cusp of celebrating 25 years of being crime free. But chaos strikes when a never-seen-before motorbike, that was purchased as a wedding gift gets stolen 7 days before the ceremony! The journey taken by the bride's family and ex-lover to find the Dupahiya forms the heart of this comedy, which explores the hopes and aspirations of simple people.
director: Avinash Dwivedi, Chirag Garg, Salona Bains Joshi, Shubh Shivdasani

title: Girls Hostel
description: Girls Hostel follows the journey of four young women—Richa, Jo, Zahira, and Mili—who navigate life in a dental college hostel. From dealing with rivalries and friendship struggles to standing up for themselves against college politics, the show humorously and insightfully explores the highs and lows of hostel life. With themes of sisterhood, empowerment, and self-discovery, it’s a relatable watch for students and young adults.\n
writer: Shreyasi Sharma, Alka Shukla, Anuya Jakatdar

title: Melo Movie
description: A movie buff falls for an aspiring director, igniting a romance that fizzles out too soon; when their paths cross again, can love find its way back?

title: The Agency
description: "The Agency" is an American spy thriller television series that follows covert CIA agent Martian, who is ordered to abandon his undercover life and return to London Station. Upon his return, he unexpectedly reunites with a past love, reigniting their romance and entangling them both in a deadly game of international intrigue and espionage. The series explores the complexities of espionage, personal relationships, and the ethical dilemmas faced by intelligence operatives.

title: Adolescence
description: "Adolescence" is a British crime drama that follows the harrowing journey of the Miller family, whose lives are upended when 13-year-old Jamie Miller is arrested for the murder of his classmate, Katie Leonard. The series delves into the complexities of teenage life, the influence of online cultures, and the challenges families face in the modern world. Each episode is uniquely presented in a single continuous take, enhancing the raw and immersive storytelling. ​

title: Running Point
description: "Running Point" is a sports comedy series that follows Isla Gordon, a reformed party girl who unexpectedly becomes the president of her family's professional basketball team, the Los Angeles Waves. As she navigates the challenges of managing a sports franchise, Isla strives to prove her capabilities in a male-dominated industry, all while dealing with family dynamics and personal growth.
director: Elaine Ko, Mindy Kaling, Ike Barinholtz, David Stassen
writer: Elaine Ko, Mindy Kaling, Ike Barinholtz, David Stassen

title: Khakee: The Bengal Chapter
description: After a respected officer's death in early 2000s Bengal, IPS Arjun Maitra confronts powerful gangsters and corrupt politicians in his mission to bring law and order to a region gripped by crime and chaos.

title: The Studio
description: "The Studio" is a satirical comedy-drama that follows Matt Remick, the newly appointed head of the struggling Continental Studios. As a passionate cinephile, Matt grapples with the challenges of balancing corporate demands with his desire to produce quality films, all while navigating the eccentricities of Hollywood's elite.
director: Seth Rogen, Evan Goldberg, Peter Huyck, Alex Gregory, Frida Perez
writer: Seth Rogen, Evan Goldberg, Peter Huyck, Alex Gregory, Frida Perez

title: Side Quest
description: "Side Quest" is an anthology comedy series and a spin-off of "Mythic Quest." Each of its four episodes delves into the lives of employees, players, and fans of the video game "Mythic Quest," exploring how the game impacts their personal and professional lives.
director: Ashly Burch, John Howell Harris, Katie McElhenney
writer: Ashly Burch, John Howell Harris, Katie McElhenney, Leann Bowen, Javier Scott

title: Your Friends & Neighbors
description: After being fired in disgrace, hedge fund manager Andrew "Coop" Cooper, grappling with his recent divorce, resorts to stealing from his neighbors’ homes in the affluent Westmont Village. As he delves deeper into this new lifestyle, Coop uncovers dangerous secrets and affairs hidden behind the wealthy facades, realizing that the lives of his neighbors might be more perilous than he ever imagined. ​
writer: Jonathan Tropper, Jennifer Yale, Josh Stoddard, Evan Endicott​

title: Government Cheese​
description: Set in 1969 San Fernando Valley, "Government Cheese" follows Hampton Chambers, a recently released ex-convict and aspiring inventor, as he attempts to reconnect with his family and pursue the American Dream. His return disrupts the unconventional family unit formed during his absence, leading to a series of surreal and comedic events.Surrealist Comedy-Drama
writer: Paul Hunter, Aeysha Carr, Hugh Moore, Wes Brown, Migizi Pensoneau, Katherine Kearns, Cece Burke

title: Carême
description: "Carême" is a French-language historical drama series that chronicles the life of Antonin Carême, considered the world's first celebrity chef. Rising from humble beginnings in post-revolutionary Paris, Carême's culinary genius propels him into the opulent courts of Napoleon's Europe. However, his ascent is complicated as powerful political figures, notably diplomat Charles-Maurice de Talleyrand-Périgord, enlist him as a spy for France. Balancing his passion for gastronomy with the perilous world of espionage, Carême navigates a treacherous path filled with ambition, romance, and political intrigue.

title: Pulse
description: "Pulse" is a medical drama series set in Miami's Maguire Medical Center, the city's busiest Level 1 trauma center. The story follows Dr. Danielle "Danny" Simms, a third-year emergency medicine resident who is thrust into the role of interim chief resident after filing a sexual harassment complaint against her superior and ex-boyfriend, Dr. Xander Phillips. As a hurricane approaches, the hospital staff navigates personal and professional challenges, including complex relationships, ethical dilemmas, and high-stakes medical emergencies.
writer: Zoe Robyn, Carlton Cuse, Ann Cherkis, Helen Childress, Shepard Boucher, Johanna Lee, Joshua Troke

title: Devil May Cry
description: Based on Capcom's iconic video game franchise, "Devil May Cry" follows Dante, a half-demon, half-human demon hunter for hire. As sinister forces threaten to merge the human and demon realms, Dante must confront powerful adversaries, including the enigmatic White Rabbit and his own long-lost brother, Vergil. Set in a stylized late '90s/early 2000s world, the series blends high-octane action with dark fantasy elements.

title: Ransom Canyon​
description: Set against the rugged backdrop of Texas Hill Country, "Ransom Canyon" is a romantic Western drama that follows the intertwined lives of three ranching families. At the center is Staten Kirkland, a stoic rancher grappling with personal loss and seeking justice. As land disputes and external threats loom, Staten's bond with longtime friend and dancehall owner Quinn O'Grady offers a glimmer of hope. The series delves into themes of love, legacy, and the complexities of family dynamics.
writer: April Blair, Joe Fazzio, Paul Haapaniemi, Laura Nava, Luca Rojas

title: Love on the Spectrum​
description: "Love on the Spectrum" is a heartfelt documentary series that follows individuals on the autism spectrum as they navigate the complexities of dating and relationships. The show offers an intimate look into their experiences, challenges, and triumphs in the pursuit of love, providing viewers with a deeper understanding of neurodiversity and the universal desire for connection.

title: The Clubhouse: A Year with the Red Sox​
description: "The Clubhouse: A Year with the Red Sox" is an immersive documentary series that provides unprecedented access to the Boston Red Sox during their 2024 MLB season. Directed by four-time Emmy winner Greg Whiteley, the series delves into the personal and professional lives of players, coaches, and executives, capturing the highs and lows of a grueling 162-game season. The documentary offers an unfiltered look at the mental and emotional challenges faced by the team, highlighting stories such as outfielder Jarren Duran's candid discussion of his mental health struggles.

title: The Four Seasons
description: A modern adaptation of the 1981 Alan Alda film, The Four Seasons follows three long-time married couples—Kate & Jack, Nick & Anne, and Danny & Claude—who uphold a cherished tradition of quarterly weekend getaways. Their decades-long friendship faces unexpected challenges when one couple announces their divorce, prompting a cascade of emotional revelations and reshaping group dynamics. The series delves into themes of love, aging, and the complexities of enduring relationships, blending heartfelt drama with gentle humor.
director: Tina Fey, Lang Fisher, Tracey Wigfield
writer: Tina Fey, Lang Fisher, Tracey Wigfield, Lisa Muse Bryant, Vali Chandrasekaran, Dylan Morgan, John Riggi, Josh Siegal, Matt Whitaker

title: Andor
description: "Andor" is a prequel series to Rogue One: A Star Wars Story, focusing on the formative years of Rebel spy Cassian Andor. The series delves into his transformation from a disillusioned thief into a key figure in the burgeoning Rebellion against the Galactic Empire. Set against a backdrop of political intrigue and oppression, "Andor" explores themes of resistance, identity, and sacrifice, offering a gritty and mature perspective within the Star Wars universe.
genre: Science Fiction, Action, Drama, Political Thriller
writer: Tony Gilroy, Dan Gilroy, Beau Willimon, Stephen Schiff

title: The Eternaut​
description: Set in Buenos Aires, "The Eternaut" follows Juan Salvo and a group of survivors after a mysterious, deadly snowfall kills millions. As they navigate the apocalyptic landscape, they uncover that the snowfall is the first wave of an alien invasion, leading them to resist an invisible threat from another world.
writer: Bruno Stagnaro, Ariel Staltari​ Tom's Guide+8

title: MobLand​
description: Set in London, "MobLand" follows the Harrigan crime family as they navigate a brutal turf war with the rival Stevenson clan. Harry Da Souza, a street-smart fixer, is tasked with protecting the Harrigans' interests and preventing an all-out gang war. As tensions escalate, Harry must confront betrayals, family secrets, and his own moral compass.

title: Murderbot
description: Based on Martha Wells’ award-winning The Murderbot Diaries, this sci-fi action comedy follows a self-aware security android, known as Murderbot, who hacks its own governor module to gain autonomy. Preferring to binge-watch soap operas rather than interact with humans, Murderbot is reluctantly assigned to protect a team of scientists on a perilous mission. As it navigates corporate conspiracies and alien threats, Murderbot grapples with its own identity and the complexities of human emotions.

title: Before
description: After the tragic loss of his wife to suicide, child psychiatrist Eli Adler encounters Noah, a troubled young boy who seems to have a haunting connection to Eli's past. As Eli attempts to help Noah, their mysterious bond deepens, leading Eli to confront his own buried traumas and the possibility of supernatural forces at play.
writer: Sarah Thorp, Emmy Grinwis, Desta Tedros Reff, Howie Miller, Joseph Sousa, Audrey Rosenberg

title: The Royals
description: Set in the fictional city of Morpur, India, "The Royals" follows Sophia Kanmani Shekhar, a driven CEO of a luxury hospitality startup, who partners with Aviraaj Singh, a polo-playing prince recently appointed as Maharaja after his father's death. Together, they aim to transform his family's crumbling palace into a high-end bed-and-breakfast. As their professional collaboration deepens, so does their personal connection, leading to a whirlwind romance amidst royal responsibilities and entrepreneurial ambitions.
director: Rangita Pritish Nandy, Ishita Pritish Nandy
writer: Neha Veena Sharma, Iti Agarwal, Vishnu Sinha

title: American Manhunt: Osama bin Laden
description: This three-part docuseries delves into the decade-long global pursuit of Osama bin Laden, the mastermind behind the September 11 attacks. Through exclusive interviews with CIA operatives, military officials, and journalists, the series uncovers the challenges and decisions faced by those tasked with bringing bin Laden to justice.

title: Poker Face
description: "Poker Face" is a mystery-of-the-week series following Charlie Cale, a casino worker with an extraordinary ability to detect lies. After a suspicious death at her workplace, Charlie hits the road in her Plymouth Barracuda, encountering a new cast of characters and strange crimes at every stop, which she can't help but solve. The series pays homage to classic detective shows like "Columbo" with its "howcatchem" format, where the audience sees the crime unfold and then watches Charlie unravel the mystery.
writer: Rian Johnson, Nora Zuckerman, Lilla Zuckerman, Tony Tost
